  "text": "Multiwalled Carbon nanotubes (MWCNTs) are excellent electrode material to realize simple, low cost and easy-to-use electrochemical sensors because of their wide electrical potential window, fast electron transfer rate and large surface area. [CITATION_1] Unmodified MWCNTs in the form of tower, array, and thread structures were used as an electrode material. These unmodified MWCNTs provided considerable simplicity in electrode fabrication compared to that of modified MWCNTs. [CITATION_2] However,",
